title: 6 US Thermold polymer date stamped preban AR-15 magazines
postcontent:
I've got 6 of these magazines to sell. They're US made Thermolds (NOT Ther"melts" that were made in Canada, with the maple leaf). These were made in the US by D&D of North Carolina. Some are date stamped (90). They are definite preban because D&D went out of business before the ban ended, so all their magazines are preban or marked LEO only (which these are not).

They are a Zytel construction (fiberglass reinforced nylon polymer) and are very sturdy.





There's one caveat with these magazines. The topmost rib is designed to prevent the magazine from being inserted too far into the rifle to prevent damage to the feed lips. On some lowers this rib prevents the magazine from being inserted fully and locking. My Anvil Arms has no problems. I have these because someone with an Olympic said they didn't fit his receiver, nor his friend's Bushmaster. If you have a mil-spec receiver these should work no problem. But the rib can be sanded down slightly to fit. I can't offer returns, so that is the warning. I'm going to try them in a DPMS and see.


$20 each plus $5 shipping. I prefer discrete Paypal, or FTF cash.

title: Wesson & Harrington 1871 Buffalo Classic
postcontent:
This rifle was purchased new in 2002 and has only had about 100-150 rounds through it. The real kicker is that it's never had a single smokeless round, nor a jacketed bullet down the barrel...EVER. I bought the rifle with the sole intention of nostalgia, and the pleasure of shooting cast lead bullets propelled by blackpowder. It is fully capable of firing all factory .45-70 ammunition including the high pressure Buffalo Bore rounds that were manufactured to duplicate the performace of the 450 marlin round. It's a stout action, and if you are a reloader, you can load this round with bullets as heavy as your shoulder will bear. It's got a 34'' barrel and a williams peep rear sight, case colored action and butt-plate. It's been well maintained, and mostly a safe queen. I've been selling off the rifles that I just don't shoot anymore which unfortunately includes this rifle. There is a minor ding on the underside of the stock that I have included a photo of, but that's it. The rest of the rifle is immaculate, and well maintained. I am including 25 rounds of Goex Black Dawge Black Powder cartridges that are 405gr RNL bullets. I recommend firing one at dusk when the light it low for a incredible fireball.

Another note, the receiver is drilled and tapped for scopes if you choose to mount optics. If you have any questions, please email or call. I'm available by phone until 11:30am CST after which i'm at work, and off all day Thursday and weekends. My name is Branden, and my cell number is REDACTED.

title: CONCEALD CARRY HOLSTER     THUNDER WEAR
postcontent:
Thunderwear was designed by a wearer. It provides a stable platform for the most comfortable, concealed carry possible. We anchor the weight around the hipbones, (not on the soft tissue of your waist). This distributes the weight of your weapon (and extra magazine) evenly around the hips at the center of gravity. The weapon is worn in the front, on the centerline. This way it will not interfere with normal or rigorous activity. When you sit down, the weapon fits down comfortably between your legs. "Sensitive" body parts are behind the bulk of the weapon. Worn on top of the underwear and shirt, but under the trousers. Be as active as you want. You'll never have to adjust your holster.

The Standard Model is made especially for the type of handgun you specify. It has a pocket on the opposite side to carry an extra Magazine. We will manufacture the Holster for a right or left handed shooter. Strap size does not matter since we make each Holster one at a time as per your specifications.

The Combination Holster is a 3 pocketed holster. The Holster can be used for right or left hand shooters. The 2 front pockets are the same size. The Combination Holster has a back pocket, directly behind the 2 front pockets. The back pocket can accommodate cash, badge, handcuffs or use your own imagination. The Combination Holster is for customers who require 1 holster for all their handguns. The Combination Holster comes in 3 sizes.

The Small Combination Holster will carry all small framed handguns. (i.e., Colt Pony, Mustang, Kel-tec P11, Walther PPK, Beretta Tomcat, Kahr-9, Sig 232 and all handguns of like size.)

The Medium Combination Holster will carry all small as mentioned of like size plus, Medium framed handguns. (i.e., All mini Glocks, Glock 23, 19, etc., Sig 239, 228, 229, All J frame Snub nose revolvers and like sized handguns.)

The Large Combination Holster (a.k.a. the "Federal Model") will carry all small, medium and Large framed handguns. (i.e., Full sized 45's, Baretta 92's, Glock 17, 21, 22, Combat Commander, Browning Hi Power and all like sized handguns.)



CALL REDACTED TO PLACE ORDER

title: Utah Non Resident permit By Rochester Personal Defense
postcontent:
Do you travel a lot? Want to carry your handgun legally in 30 states? The State of Utah has redone their Non Resident Permit process and you get the benefit. We are now certified to instruct you in the legalities and carrying of a firearm in Utah as well as the other states that honor the Utah Non-Resident Permit. If you travel a lot, the non-resident permits are a big help if you decide to carry or wish to carry where you want to go. Note: the Utah permit is NOT VALID IN NEW YORK STATE.

NOTE: This class will cover ONLY the laws and regulations concerning the State of Utah. We will not be discussing New York State laws or other states' laws. If you possess a NY State Pistol Permit, thank you, but it will neither help you nor hurt you when applying for the Utah permit. There is no way to obtain a waiver or exclusion to the lecture. Utah requires you to attend no matter what your experience or training is.

Classes are currently available from Rochester Personal Defense in the following areas: Rochester, Syracuse, Binghamton, Middletown, Dansville, Penfield, Henrietta, Brockport, Batavia, Auburn, Oswego, Watertown, Waterloo, Chenango County, Broome County, Tioga County, Monroe County, Northern Pennsylvania, AND MORE!!!!

We will be doing your passport style photos, processing your fingerprints, and we have a notary available. All you have to do is attend, add a copy of your NY drivers license, a check made payable to the Utah BCI for $65.25, and fill everything out and drop your completed application (with your payment) in the mail. We even give you the pre addressed envelope!!

The Utah Non-Resident permit is as good as the Florida permit, but you get a couple different states that Florida does not give you. Also, the cost of the permit itself is only $65.20 and it is valid for 5 years. Note: the class fee does not include the cost of the permit.

There are some disqualifiers too. (DWI's within 10 yrs, etc) Please contact us if you have any questions before registering. (We'd hate to have you come attend and be surprised).

The following states currently honor the Utah Non Resident permit:  Alabama, Alaska, Arizona, Arkansas, Delaware, Georgia, Idaho, Indiana, Kentucky, Louisiana, Minnesota, Mississippi, Missouri, Montana, Nevada, New Mexico, North Carolina, North Dakota, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, South Dakota, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, Utah, Vermont, Virginia, Washington, Wyoming (info taken from www.USAcarry.com, 3-16-09)

title: Concealed Carry Permit Training class by Rochester Personal Defense
postcontent:
Rochester Personal Defense is now providing the above class to include the required components needed to seek your "Unrestricted" NY State Permit through the court system. 

This class is the ONLY class offered in the area in which you will receive actual training, not just a performance certification. 

You will learn valuable but necessary skills that will not only help you carry your firearm more securely and more reliably, but possibly save your life. This training is the most comprehensive class you will find in the area. If you are going to seek a way to upgrade your permit, why not go with the class that will actually teach you the skills you will need to carry concealed, know when to fight and more importantly, know when NOT to fight. You will not only learn about the legalities and other important topics, you will be a better shooter when you get done!

Judge Sullivan of Chenango County will issue your upgrade based on this course!!!
Judge Segulia has also issued permits based on this class.

Here's a partial list of topics and skills that you will learn during this course:
Firearm safety, storage, and cleaning
Legalities and justification in self defense (Article 35)
Avoiding potentially dangerous situations
De-escalation and disengagement during a Critical Incident
Moral decisions about owning, carrying, and using a firearm
How to draw and present the handgun safely and effectively
Shooting skills and marksmanship instruction
Malfunctions and stoppage clearing

Equipment Required: Eye and ear protection, A working and reliable firearm of a defensive nature, (NO hunting or target guns) Approximately 150 rounds of ammunition, minimum of 2 magazines or speedloaders with carriers, a quality strong side, belt mounted  type holster (NO shoulder holsters please), comfortable footwear and weather appropriate clothing.

Prerequisites: NY State Pistol permit and NRA Basic Pistol or equivalent training/shooting experience

title: Utah Non Resident permit By Rochester Personal Defense
postcontent:
Do you travel a lot? Want to carry your handgun legally in 30 states? The State of Utah has redone their Non Resident Permit process and you get the benefit. We are now certified to instruct you in the legalities and carrying of a firearm in Utah as well as the other states that honor the Utah Non-Resident Permit. If you travel a lot, the non-resident permits are a big help if you decide to carry or wish to carry where you want to go. Note: the Utah permit is NOT VALID IN NEW YORK STATE.

NOTE: This class will cover ONLY the laws and regulations concerning the State of Utah. We will not be discussing New York State laws or other states' laws. If you possess a NY State Pistol Permit, thank you, but it will neither help you nor hurt you when applying for the Utah permit. There is no way to obtain a waiver or exclusion to the lecture. Utah requires you to attend no matter what your experience or training is.

Classes are currently available from Rochester Personal Defense in the following areas: Rochester, Syracuse, Binghamton, Middletown, Dansville, Penfield, Henrietta, Brockport, Batavia, Auburn, Oswego, Watertown, Waterloo, Chenango County, Broome County, Tioga County, Monroe County, Northern Pennsylvania, AND MORE!!!!

We will be doing your passport style photos, processing your fingerprints, and we have a notary available. All you have to do is attend, add a copy of your NY drivers license, a check made payable to the Utah BCI for $65.25, and fill everything out and drop your completed application (with your payment) in the mail. We even give you the pre addressed envelope!!

The Utah Non-Resident permit is as good as the Florida permit, but you get a couple different states that Florida does not give you. Also, the cost of the permit itself is only $65.20 and it is valid for 5 years. Note: the class fee does not include the cost of the permit.

There are some disqualifiers too. (DWI's within 10 yrs, etc) Please contact us if you have any questions before registering. (We'd hate to have you come attend and be surprised).

The following states currently honor the Utah Non Resident permit: Alabama, Alaska, Arizona, Arkansas, Delaware, Georgia, Idaho, Indiana, Kentucky, Louisiana, Minnesota, Mississippi, Missouri, Montana, Nevada, New Mexico, North Carolina, North Dakota, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, South Dakota, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, Utah, Vermont, Virginia, Washington, Wyoming (info taken from www.USAcarry.com, 3-16-09)

Upcoming lecture dates:

May 30 and 31, June 7, 12, 22, July 12....more being added every day

title: Michigan Open Carry Picnic
postcontent:
What:  MOC Picnic and 2nd Amendment March Town Hall Meeting.
Where: Sunset Park, Traverse City, MI
When: Saturday June 27th at Noon to 4:00 PM or whenever.
Why:  For good friends, good food and to learn more about the 2nd Amd. March next April.
Who:  MOC and the Second Amendment March.

Contacts: Brian Jeffs, President of MOC---Skip Coryell, SA March founder and organizer.

Please set aside this date for a great gathering of friends and patriots.  Bring food to cook or a dish to pass.  Also bring your own tableware, beverages, and a few portable chairs if desired.  MOC staff will supply the charcoal, condiments, grills and some meats (hot-dogs, burgers, and brats).  This is a family friendly get together and you don't have to OC if you don't want to.  Come out and have some fun and learn more about OC and the March on DC. 

Dress for and bring things you need for a day at the beach.  Sun-Set Park is between the Holiday Inn on the west and the Great Lakes Maritime Academy on the east.  It's a great location for swimming and you can fish on the Maritime Pier.  There are plenty of picnic tables, but a lawn chair is more comfortable.  Parking is on the east side of the park.  

A March representative will speak at the picnic and talk about the March followed by some Q&A.

We will be contacting the media and most likely will get a spot on the Norm Jone's Show on AM radio in TC.  Norm has helped us in the past and he might even show up at the event.

title: .30 M1 Carbine with lots of extras -- scope mount, mags, ammo, etc.
postcontent: This is a .30 caliber M1 Carbine, made by Universal Arms of Hialeah, FL.  It is in good condition, and shoots nice, tight groups.  Bore is bright and perfect.  It has the adjustable windage/elevation rear aperture sight.  It also comes with a picatinny rail scope mount and 1" rings, three 15-round mags, a GI sling, a GI mag pouch for the stock, and a GI cleaning kit that goes in the stock for the sling to loop around.  It doesn't come with a scope... the one that was on it when i bought it was a big long hunting scope, and the lens came too far back over the stock to assume a proper shooting position.  This mount would work great with a shorter scope.  This rifle also comes with most of a 50 round box of FMJ ammo, and about 30 rounds of soft points.  Ammo is cheap for these things right now... you can get a 500 round case for $155 from CMP.  These things have nice low recoil, but still pack a punch.  Ballistics similar to a .357 mag out of a compact little carbine.  Great for everything -- plinking, hunting, personal defense, paper punching, whatever.  This thing has been really well taken care of too... not a spot of rust on it, and it hasn't been fired hardly at all in the past 15 years.  I recently bought it from a friend who needed money... he inherited it from his grandpa and its mostly been sitting in a closet.  I am in Stillwater most of the time, but I can meet you anywhere reasonably close.  If you have any questions or you want to look at it, you can call me at REDACTED, or e-mail me at REDACTED.  My name is Daniel.
